# Testing Rules for DungeonFighter-v2

## Running Tests

From `Code/`:

```bash
dotnet run -- --run-tests              # full comprehensive suite
dotnet run -- --run-game-system-tests  # game-system runner only
dotnet run -- --run-data-tests         # data runner only
dotnet run -- --list-test-suites       # list filterable suite names
dotnet run -- --run-test-filter <pattern>   # run matching suites only
```

Filter examples (usable from chat prompts — ask the agent to run these):

```bash
dotnet run -- --run-test-filter FundamentalsSimulation
dotnet run -- --run-test-filter EnemyProgressionCurveEvaluator
dotnet run -- --run-test-filter game-system:Tuning
dotnet run -- --run-test-filter data:EnemyLoader
```

Patterns match suite names (substring, case-insensitive). Prefix with `game-system:` or `data:` to limit scope.

## Testing Strategy
Always follow the testing strategy:

1. **Unit Tests**: Test individual components
2. **Integration Tests**: Test system interactions
3. **Balance Tests**: Verify game balance
4. **Performance Tests**: Check execution time and memory
5. **User Acceptance Tests**: End-to-end scenarios

## Test Categories
Use the built-in test suite:
